node.accessibility_caption: Photo by @laurag_143 on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, baby, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
My arms may be full but my heart is much fuller 💕❤️💕 I absolutely love being a mom, it’s my favorite title EVER!! 🥰

It’s been 37 days since Myla has blessed us 😍🙏🏼 & I’m so obsessed with her, well with both my girls 👧🏻 👶🏻 …but I’m still trying to adjust to being a mom of 2. At times I feel like I have it all together & other times it’s complete chaos 🤪 I’ll admit, I’ve struggled trying to keep up with it all (my career, health, home, being a great partner, mom, daughter, sister, friend, the guilt of not doing enough etc.) but I realized that it’s okay to not have it all together everyday. The important part is that I’m trying my best & small progress is still progress! So I’m trying to not be so hard on myself & to soak up every moment I can with my girls. It is true what they say, they grow up so fast 🥺

To any mamas out there feeling the same way, hang in there! You got this. It won’t be like this forever. I’m here for you ❤️❤️ Love you all so much!! 😘

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by @laurag_143 on July 05, 2021 tagging @dhar.mann. May be an image of 3 people, child, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: 15 days ago (6/20 Father’s Day) we welcomed our second babygirl Myla Sky Mann into the world 🌎 ❤️ She was 5lbs & 19inch long …she looks just like her daddy  @dhar.mann 😍  I can’t even put into words the joy that I feel 🥰😍😀 I literally get so teary eyed thinking about my little family 🥺❤️ Thank you God for blessing me with two precious girls & my dream Mann 🙏🏼

node.text: It’s go time 😱😍 Of course Myla Sky would want to make her apprearance on Father’s Day 👨‍👧💙 who wouldn’t want to be Daddy’s girl when you have a daddy like @dhar.mann 🥰 Thank you God for blessing us with our soon to be family of 4 🙏🏽❤️ We will update you guys soon, say a prayer for us ❤️

node.text:
How it’s going vs how it started 🥰 Swipe all the way to see our very first IG photo together 📸 👫 & then we decided to make it an annual tradition 🥰 (We have all but 2020, since it was closed due to the pandmc). Funny how I’m pregnant in the last two recent pictures 🤰🏻haha I had no idea I was pregnant with Ella at the time (pink dress) & this time around the champagne was obviously for Dhar 🥂

So...let me tell you about this MANN who was born 37 years ago on this date, he is not only tall, DHARk, and handsome but kind, sweet, passionate, ambitious, generous, smart, loving, & is literally changing lives 👏🏻❤️ He’s not only my happy place by also my safe place, my biggest motivator, mentor, cheerleader, partner in everything, soulmate, ka-utest daddy to our babygirl, and if you can’t tell by now, he’s my everything & I can go on forever about him 🙌🏼😍 Some of you may know him as @dhar.mann but I know him as my Shnookies 🥰 

Happy Birthday Shnookies, we’ve been up, down, and all around but our journey has taught me soooo much & I couldn’t imagine being on this ride with anyone else. Thank you for loving me, Ella & Myla the way that you do. We are so lucky!! Wishing you everything that your heart desires because you truly deserve it plus more. May you be blessed with good health, great outcomes, amazing opportunities, infinite happiness, awesome new storylines and lots & lots of kisses & love from Ella, Myla, & I. We love you sooooo much ❤️

node.text:
Dear Ella, 
Although I gave you life, I feel like you really gave me mine. You put everything into perspective & made me feel emotions I never knew I could. I’m so thankful to be your mama, I promise to always love, protect, and teach you as best as I can. I love you so much babygirl & I know you are going to be a great big sister to Myla Sky ❤️ 

Wishing all the mama’s, soon to be mama’s, those hoping to be mama’s & grieving mama’s a beautiful Mother’s Day 💐❤️❤️❤️

And special thanks to my amazing baby daddy @dhar.mann for giving me Ella Rose & soon Myla Sky 🙏🏼❤️
